bytes.body:
When building on the_graph, you can now replace Ethers with Viem, a TypeScript-first, lightweight, and low-level library. Viem provides better performance and a more concise API. To migrate, you'll need to update your queries to use Viem's `createClient` function, which accepts the same options as `the_graph's` `graphqlClient`.

const viemClient = createClient({ url: 'https://api.thegraph.com/subgraphs/name/your-subgraph' });
const query = gql` query { ... } `;
viejClient.query({ query });

Viem's query builder is designed for complex queries, so you may need to refactor your existing queries to take advantage of its features.

